			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Two of the named wurms are relatively common in the Burning Woods, Glyton (typically around the Skyfire zone) and Azdalin (typically south of the Giant Fortress).  Xyfyl is said to be a rare spawn, but I've not seen him.  There are two other ways to get his scale though, from his hidden form in the Temple of Solusek Ro as Lord Lyfyx of Burwood (get it? GET IT? sheesh.)<BR>
<BR>
Method 1: pull him to the zone and kill him.  Nasty faction hits with the Temple for this, I know one fellow who went from amiable right to dubious.  He apparently does not always drop the scale.<BR>
<BR>
Method 2: Give him one peridot and one &quot;Tektite&quot;, he gives you the scale.  Tektite drops from a gargoyle at the gates in Overthere, the one called (appropriately enough) Tektite.  He can be harmony pulled, have a level 50+ harmonier harmony the other 3 gargs then pull him past.  Pull him a goodly distance away, and make sure you aren't doing this around sundown when the General and his Dragoons take their walk.  Tektite is level 50, completely resistant to magic, and hits in the 120 range.  Pets, tanks and damage shields all work fine.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
