			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				having done this incredibly annoying quest 4 times now, i figured i'd recap the thing here and throw in some added info<BR>
<BR>
step one: burning woods<BR>
enalton is a named wurm that spawns around skyfire/giant fort area. kill him, gylton spawns in the same general area<BR>
kill gylton (lore scale #1) and gullerback spawns in the area around the crater that is out front of the giant fort ramp<BR>
killer gullerback and azdalin spawn in the SW corner of the zone. kill him for lore scale #2<BR>
<BR>
step two: overthere, temple of solusek ro<BR>
find tektite the gargoyle in the outpost (by the skeleton marines, capt. rottgrime) give him 2 carnelians and he gives you a piece of tektite<BR>
give that piece of tektite and a peridot to that paladin guy for the xyfil scale (don't recall name) in the temple of sol ro, he's over by the gnome and high elf who gives the mage quests<BR>
<BR>
step three: fiorna vie<BR>
this is the most damned annoying part of this quest. in my experience hobble spawns pretty randomly anywhere between the FV bridge and the DL tunnel<BR>
best place to park a tracker is at the iksar statue by the waterfall, just in front of the DL zone<BR>
hail him and squire fuzzynuts comes running out to meet him. this is where the quest gets annoying as hell<BR>
hobble has this habit of being butchered by the drachnids... or for that matter just about anything in the zone<BR>
if you find him, follow him and protect him. if you have a tracker, after hobble is found follow him while the tracker follows fuzzynuts<BR>
contrary to other posts, it is my experience if they're fighting fuzzynuts will NOT take the scales, you have to do it while he's walking<BR>
<BR>
a note about hobble:<BR>
if he dies, which often happens, to NPC's in the zone he should respawn within 20 minutes<BR>
if, by some ungodly miracle, he doesn't die... he despawns after about 20 minutes, and won't pop again for about 6 hours<BR>
<BR>
sateryn<BR>
52 magician<BR>
innoruuk
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
